==English==

===Etymology===
Coined by [[w:L. Ron Hubbard|L. Ron Hubbard]], possibly from [[turbulent]] or [[disturbed]].

===Verb===
'''enturbulate'''
# To [[agitate]] or [[disturb]]; to [[upset]]. 
# To [[provoke]] or [[harass]]. (This usage appears more common when members of the
[[cult]] of [[Scientology]] are confronted by any of the many critics of their [[cult]].)


===Adjective===
'''enturbulated'''
# In a state of [[agitation]] or [[disturbance]]; [[turbulent]].
# In [[turmoil]].

===Usage Note===
This word is a [[shibboleth]] used exclusively by members or former members of the [[cult]] of [Scientology]], and should not be used in formal or written contexts. In modern English the use of enturbulate is non-standard 
and despite being widespread in the [[cult]] of [[Scientology]], and the misguided writings of Lafayette Ronald Hubbard, it's use should be avoided.

